# Early return ‚Äî no trailing `else`

When an `if` branch ends in `return`, `throw`, `continue`, or `break`, **do not** wrap the rest of the method in an `else` block. Let control fall through.

## Preferred

```csharp
public string Resolve(Tenant tenant)
{
    if (tenant is null) throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(tenant));
    if (!tenant.IsActive) return "(inactive)";

    return Format(tenant);
}
```

```csharp
foreach (string key in keys)
{
    if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(key)) continue;

    Process(key);
}
```

## Avoid

```csharp
// Avoid: trailing else after a return / throw
public string Resolve(Tenant tenant)
{
    if (tenant is null)
    {
        throw new ArgumentNullException(nameof(tenant));
    }
    else if (!tenant.IsActive)
    {
        return "(inactive)";
    }
    else
    {
        return Format(tenant);
    }
}
```

```csharp
// Avoid: nesting the happy path inside else
foreach (string key in keys)
{
    if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(key))
    {
        continue;
    }
    else
    {
        Process(key);
    }
}
```

## Scope

- Apply whenever the `if` branch terminates the current control flow (`return`, `throw`, `continue`, `break`, `goto`).
- Combines with **`CSharp-Terse-01-GuardClausesSameLine.mdc`**, **`SingleLineThrowNoBraces.mdc`**, and **`SingleLineContinueNoBraces.mdc`** to keep the **happy path** flat and at the bottom of the member.
- Stay with `if` / `else if` / `else` only when **every** branch produces a value at the same level (typical for switch-expression-style mappings ‚Äî and in that case, prefer **`CSharp-Terse-03-SwitchExpressions.mdc`**).
